# WhatsFresh

WhatsFresh is an API facilitating the Tracking of Ingredients into Products for small Consumer Packeged Goods makers.  It is an Account-based system.  In order to access or update data a subscription to an account must be authenticated.

# Group Authentication

# Group Company

## Brands [/brands]

Resource related to the Brands (associated to Ingredient Batches) of an account.

## Vendors [/vendors]

Resource related to the Vendors (associated to Ingredient Batches) used by an account.

## Workers [/workers]

Resource related to the Workers (a.k.a. Team Members) associated to an account.  These people perform tasks and may or may not be registered users of the WhatsFresh App.

## Users [/users]

Resource related to the Users associated to an account.  These people are registered users of the WhatsFresh App.

# Group Ingredients

Ingredients-related data.

## Ingredient Types [/ingredientTypes/{?id}]

Resource related to the ingredient types of an account.  It has the following attributes:

- name
- description

+ Parameters
    + id (optional, number) - Non-Intelligent ID.
    + account_id (required, number) - foreign key to associated account.

### List all Ingredient Types [GET]

+ Request (application/json)

    + Header

            Accept: application/json
            
+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Header

            Location: /ingredientTypes/1

### Retrieve an Ingredient Type [GET]

+ Request (application/json)

    + Header

            Accept: application/json
            
+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Header

            Location: /ingredientTypes/{id}
            
### Create a New Ingredient Type [POST]

+ Request (application/json)

    + Header

            Accept: application/json
            
+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Header

            Location: /ingredientTypes/
            
### Update an Existing Ingredient Type [PUT]

+ Request (application/json)

    + Header

            Accept: application/json
            
+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Header

            Location: /ingredientTypes/{id}
            
### Delete an Ingredient Type [DELETE]

## Ingredients [/ingredients]

